    "body" : "<p>Simplest Solution With Simple Date Format: \n<strong>SimpleDateFormat(\"ZZZZZ\"):</strong></p>\n\n<pre><code> Calendar calendar = Calendar.getInstance(TimeZone.getTimeZone(\"GMT\"),\n                Locale.getDefault());\n        Date currentLocalTime = calendar.getTime();\n\n        DateFormat date = new SimpleDateFormat(\"ZZZZZ\",Locale.getDefault());\n        String localTime = date.format(currentLocalTime);\n        System.out.println(localTime+ \"  TimeZone   \" );\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>==> Output is : +05:30 </p>\n"
